Why this test was removed from JanusGraphTest.java? Tests in JanusGraphTest.java are executed against different storages backends. I guess, it would be better to just fix this test instead of removing it.
I.e. we could change this method to something like:
@Test
public void testHasNot() {
    graph.addVertex();
    assertTrue(graph.query().hasNot("abcd").vertices().iterator().hasNext());
    assertFalse(graph.query().hasNot("abcd", true).vertices().iterator().hasNext());
}

